        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 28 at 3:14AM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 312 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Malta, or 8 miles northwest of DeKalb, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lindenwood, Valley View, Fairdale, Lily Lake, Kaneville, Aurora, West
Dundee, Genoa, South Elgin, Byron, Mount Morris, Gilberts, Kirkland,
Rochelle, DeKalb, Wayne, St. Charles, Creston, Sleepy Hollow, Oregon,
Carpentersville, Elburn, North Aurora, Geneva, and Kingston.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead
to ponding in poor drainage areas. Do not drive your vehicle through
flooded roadways.</instruction>
